I managed to create the connection between the two. I looked at the SavePasswordConfigurationBar Class and noticed the same format as mentioned in one of your older posts.

I made the first simple changes to change the text. After that I also modified the way the widget is created to suit our needs. I noticed in the SavePassConfig bar that upon calling createWidget there was no good way of changing the labels. My idea was to listen for the change of channel-error, set the label's text value and create the widget afterwards so that the error message varies. Also I deleted the listener from the infobar for the 'response' action since I figured it is probably unecessary in my case. 

I am aware of the fact that when creating a Gtk. Button you need to input the action name as well, which I'm sure connects the action to other functions in telepathy client. What I am not aware of is how exactly does that happen.

I also have a problem where the 'Retry' button is not clickable, but I'm thinking it is because I haven't properly assigned an action to it.

My new Class looks like this at the moment:
```
const ChannelErrorBar = GObject.registerClass(
class ChannelErrorBar extends Gtk.Revealer {
    _init(room) {
        this._room = room;

        super._init({ valign: Gtk.Align.START });

        this.connect('destroy', this._onDestroy.bind(this));

        this._room.connect('notify::channel-error', () => {
            debug('***EVENT CAUGHT as ' + room.channel_error + ' in channelErrorBar');
            this.error_type = room.channel_error;
            this._createWidget();
            this.reveal_child = true;

            this._infoBar.connect('response', (w, res) => {
            this.reveal_child = false;
           });
        });
    }

    _createWidget() {
        this._infoBar = new Gtk.InfoBar({ show_close_button: true });
        this.add(this._infoBar);

        let target = new GLib.Variant('o', this._room.account.object_path);
        let button = new Gtk.Button({ label: _("_Retry"),
                                      use_underline: true,
                                      action_name: 'app.retry-channel-connection',
                                      action_target: target });
        this._infoBar.add_action_widget(button, Gtk.ResponseType.ACCEPT);

        let box = new Gtk.Box({ orientation: Gtk.Orientation.VERTICAL });
        this._infoBar.get_content_area().add(box);

        let title = _("Failed to join the room.");
        this._titleLabel = new Gtk.Label({ halign: Gtk.Align.START,
                                           valign: Gtk.Align.CENTER,
                                           wrap: true });
        this._titleLabel.set_markup(`<b>${title}</b>`);
        box.add(this._titleLabel);

        let text = _("ERROR: " + this.error_type);
        this._subtitleLabel = new Gtk.Label({ label: text,
                                              ellipsize: Pango.EllipsizeMode.END });
        box.add(this._subtitleLabel);

        this._infoBar.show_all();
    }

    _onDestroy() {
        if (this._identifySentId)
            this._room.disconnect(this._identifySentId);
        this._identifySentId = 0;
    }
});

```

